This was when artists like Elvis Presley, Chuck Berry, Little Richard, and Jerry Lee Lewis rose to fame with their energetic performances and hit songs that captured the spirit of youth rebellion and freedom.

Therefore, it can be said that rock 'n' roll began to emerge and gain popularity in the mid-1950s, although its roots can be traced back to earlier musical styles and influences.
